<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Italy-TunnelFire     07-26 0099</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Italy-Tunnel Fire,0102</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Train Burns In Tunnel; One Dead, 20 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORVIETO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train stalled in a tunnel after catching
fire and one man suffocated while 20 other passengers were treated
for smoke inhalation, railroad officials reported.
   They said the train was en route to Bolzano from Rome and was
carrying more than 150 passengers when the incident occurred Monday.
   The officials said the cause of the fire has not been
determined. Area residents alerted authorities when they saw smoke
pouring from the tunnel.
   Officials said Romeo Ascioni, 64, of Rome, died of suffocation.
</TEXT>
