<1ST_LINE>u i AM-JapanMarkets     07-26 0143</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan Markets,0147</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar Up Slightly</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar gained slightly against the Japanese
yen, while share prices rebounded in slow trading Tuesday as market
players awaited news of American GNP figures.
   The dollar opened at 132.25 yen and rose to 132.60 yen before
edging down to close at 132.15 yen, up 0.35 yen from Monday's close
of 131.80 yen.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, which shed
117.81 points Monday, gained 120.23 points or 0.44 percent to close
at 27,303.76 in thin trading.
   Many investors were taking a wait-and-see attitude in advance of
the report on second quarter U.S. gross national product.
   ``If the U.S. GNP number is too strong, people are concerned
about inflation in the United States,'' said Hisamichi Sawa of
Prudential Bache.
   ``Trading is directionless,'' said an exchange dealer, speaking
on condition of anonymity.

</TEXT>
