<1ST_LINE>d a PM-ShowShooting     07-26 0214</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Show Shooting,0220</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Accidently Shoots Friend After Gun Show</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PENSACOLA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A dummy round kept an automatic pistol
from firing when Benjamin Crewshaw pointed the gun at a friend and
pulled the trigger.
   ``OK, shoot me,'' Donald Glen Mora, 23, told his friend, said
Sgt. Lee Wasdin of the Escambia County Sheriff's Department.
   Crewshaw, 25, pulled back the slide on the gun and it ejected
the dummy round. When he pulled the trigger again, a live bullet
fired, hitting Mora in the lower right chest, killing him, Wasdin
said Monday.
   ``He had forgotten he had a loaded clip in the gun behind the
dummy round,'' Wasdin said.
   Crewshaw had bought the dummy round, a safety extender, barrel
extender and a cleaning rod at the Pensacola Gun and Knife Show at
Bayfront Auditorium on Sunday.
   ``When he put the barrel extender on, the weapon was not sliding
properly, so he was examining it to see what was wrong with it,''
Wasdin said.
   At that point, Mora and two friends showed up at Crewshaw's
door, asking to borrow a part for a car. While they were talking,
Crewshaw aimed the .45 caliber automatic at Mora, Wasdin said.
   The shooting, although considered accidental, remains under
investigation, Wasdin said. No charges have been filed.
</TEXT>
