<HEAD>8-Year-Old and Accomplice Arrested on Attempted Armed Robbery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEERFIELD BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman walking to her car in the
parking lot of a bank thought it was a joke when an 8-year-old told
her to hand over her money or he'd kill her.
   When she refused, the youngster flashed a knife. She ran to her
van. He threw the knife at her as she drove off.
   ``I just thought it was a kid messing around, so I told him to
beat it,'' said Sandra Lamusta. ``Then he pulled out a knife, and I
took him seriously.''
   Ms. Lamusta drove to a nearby convenience store and called
police, who arrested the boy and a 12-year-old friend a short time
later.
   The two boys were charged with attempted armed robbery, said Lt.
F.M. Adams. Police could not release the suspects' names because
they are juveniles.
   ``It's sort of discouraging to think that our society has gotten
that bad,'' said Adams. ``It tells me our whole system is out of
whack.''
   Ms. Lamusta, a mother of three adult children, said she could
not believe it either. ``Kids do strange things,'' she said. ``It
upset me.''
   Ms. Lamusta told police she had seen the boys sitting under a
tree when she first pulled up at the bank.
   ``It's a busy intersection there,'' she said. ``It never
occurred to me that anyone would be up to any shenanigans.''
