<FILEID>AP-NR-07-26-88 0939EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--TrainAccident     07-26 0102</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Train Accident,0105</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Passenger Train Collides With Locomotive, 30 Injured</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Retransmitting a0531 to CORRECT category code.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger train collided with a
locomotive engine in suburban Brussels today, injuring 30 people,
officials said.
   Some passengers suffered broken bones, according to Louis
Gillieaux, a spokesman for the Belgian railways. He said most
injuries were minor.
   The train from Brussels hit the side of the locomotive at 10:30
a.m. just outside the station of Braine-Le-Compte, about 6 miles
south of Brussels.
   ``The locomotive was somewhere where it should not have been,''
said Hugo Van Herle, another railway spokesman.
</TEXT>
