<HEAD>Paraguay Expells Spanish Priest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASUNCION, Paraguay (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government expelled a Spanish
Jesuit priest for his recent remarks in favor of liberation
theology, the Roman Catholic radio station Caritas reported.
   Juan Antonio de la Vega, 65, was escorted by police Monday
across a bridge into the Argentine town of Clorinda, according to a
