<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Sierra Leone,0130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ex-Officials Convicted of Defrauding Government</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FREETOWN, Sierra Leone (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A court Tuesday convicted two
former Ministry of Finance officials and a businessman on fraud
charges, and gave them the option of a three-year prison term or
fines of about $5,500 each.
   Christie Green, former minister of state, and Mohammed Nallo, a
former assistant finance secretary, chose to pay the fines.
   The third defendant, businessman Bankole Macauley, has fled the
country. He was tried in absentia.
   They were convicted of conspiring to defraud the government and
causing it to make illegal payments to certain individuals.
   The three were the first to be tried among 32 former civil
servants, bankers and businessmen who were charged in May with
defrauding the government of about $800,000.
