<HEAD>Honorary Austrian Consul General Dies Of Heart Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Walter H. Bunzl, Austria's honorary consul
general in Atlanta since 1967, has died of a heart attack at age 75.
   Bunzl, born in Austria, came to Atlanta in 1939 after Germany
occupied his homeland. He operated a travel agency here from 1967
until 1986. His territory as consul general covered six Southern
states.
   He succeeded his father, the late Robert Bunzl, in the post,
which is unpaid.
   He died Thursday at Northside Hospital as he was getting dressed
after a routine medical examination. Family members said he had no
history of heart trouble.
   Bunzl was treasurer of the Atlanta Consular Corps and was active
in symphonic and other cultural activities.
   Survivors include his wife, Frances Hamburger Bunzl, two
children and a brother.
</TEXT>
