<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Tuesday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   GEORGE BUSH, breaking with the Reagan administration by calling
for legislation applying the independent counsel law to Congress:
``Those who take on the people's trust must hold themselves to an
exacting code of conduct. We can expect, and indeed, tolerate
nothing less from the people who work for the government.''
   
   New Hampshire Gov. JOHN SUNUNU, acknowledging Bush sent him
questionnaire forms used in the vice president's search for a
running mate, but refusing to elaborate further: ``I have no
comments on this at this time at all.''
   
   PRESIDENT REAGAN, lambasting Democrats for taking shots at his
administration last week during the Democratic National Convention:
``To hear the opposition talk, you would think growth in our
economy had come to a dead halt.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, saying Reagan should have asked for Attorney
General Edwin Meese's resignation in April after two former Justice
Department officials told the president and Bush that they believed
Meese violated the law: ``I hope I never have a briefing like the
one Mr. Burns and Mr. Weld gave the vice president three months
ago. But if I do, I won't sit there and do nothing.''
