<HEAD>European Parliament Elections Set For Next June 15, 18</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Elections to the European Parliament
will take place June 15 and 18 next year, European Economic
Comunity ministers decided Tuesday after consulting with
parliamentarians, it was officially reported.
   The vote will take place on Thursday June 15 in countries where
elections are held on a weekday _ Britain, the Netherlands, Denmark
and Ireland _ and on Sunday June 18 in the eight other EEC member
states _ West Germany, France, Italy, Spain, Greece, Portugal,
Belgium and Luxembourg.
   This will be the third time that the 518-member European
parliamentary assembly, which sits in Strasbourg, France, will be
directly elected.
   Its first direct election took place in 1979. It is held every
five years.
