<2ND_LINE>AM-Chile-Quake,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quake Hits Central Chile; No Victims or Damage Reported</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An earthquake rocked central Chile
Tuesday evening but no victims or damage were reported, authorities
said.
   The quake measured 4.8 on the Richter scale, according to the
Seismological Institute of the University of Chile in Santiago.
   It was felt in an area about 125 miles long in central Chile,
including Santiago, the capital city of 4.5 million people.
   The Richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on a
seismograph. Every increase of one number means a tenfold increase
in magnitude.
   An earthquake measuring 4 on the Richter scale can cause
moderate damage, and one measuring 5 can cause considerable damage.
