<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Britain-Earns-Banks     07-26 0196</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Earns-Banks,0204</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>National Westminster Earnings Nearly Triple from Weak Year-ago
Results</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   National Westminster Bank PLC, one of Britain's
largest banks, said Tuesday its half-year earnings nearly tripled
from a year earlier, when its results were hurt by major additions
to provisions for loans to developing countries.
   The bank said earnings for the six months ended June 30
increased to 446 million pounds, the equivalent of $767 million, or
59 pence a share, from 150 million pounds, or 20 pence a share, a
year ago.
   National Westminster added 6 million pounds to its provisions
for developing country loans in the first half of 1988, compared
with 496 million pounds in the same period last year.
   Total income, which includes interest, commission, investment
and foreign exchange trading income, grew 15 percent to 2.34
billion pounds from 2.04 billion pounds.
   Investment banking continued to be a troublesome area for
National Westminster, in part because of the depressed securities
markets. Investment banking operations had a pre-tax loss of 10
million pounds, compared with a 2 million-pound pre-tax profit a
year ago.
   National Westminster's total assets rose 19 percent to 102.5
billion pounds from 86.3 billion pounds.
</TEXT>
