<HEAD>Posts 11 Perecent Profit Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BETHESDA, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Martin Marietta Corp. said Tuesday its
second-quarter profit rose about 11 percent on a revenue increase
of 3.6 percent.
   The aerospace contractor reported earnings of $81.4 million, or
$1.53 per share, in the second quarter compared with $71.6 million,
or $1.31 per share, in the second quarter of 1987.
   Sales for the second quarter rose to $1.44 billion from $1.39
billion a year ago, the company reported.
   Six-month net earnings rose 13.8 percent to $132.4 million, or
$2.49 per share, compared with $115.6 million, or $2.11 per share,
for the first half of 1987.
   Sales for the first half of the year rose 8.3 percent to $2.74
billion, compared with $2.53 billion the same period of 1987.
