<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Stocks Slip</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates thruout with closing figures and comment.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices finished fractionally lower Tuesday in slow
trading on the London Stock Exchange as traders awaited more
evidence on the British economy.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 0.8
point, or 0.04 percent, to 1,837.7.
   Volume rose to 338 million shares, up from 288.4 million issues
on Monday.
   Market watchers said traders were waiting for the British
balance of payments report for June, due for release Wednesday.
   Wednesday's scheduled release of preliminary U.S. gross national
product figures for the second quarter also kept many London
trdaers cautious, dealers said.
   However, several dealers said the economic reports might be
overlooked by the summer market.
   ``No matter what the figures are, I think we're resigned to
drift sideways until the end of August,'' one salesman said.
</TEXT>
