<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street Closing,0149</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices struggled to a small gain in light
trading today, continuing Monday's erratic pattern.
   Analysts said many investors were avoiding making big
commitments in advance of the Commerce Department's report due out
Wednesday on the gross national product for the second quarter of
the year.
   Private estimates generally call for inflation-adjusted GNP
growth to come in at about the same 3.6 percent annual rate
reported for the first quarter.
   Anything much higher than that might intensify worries about
inflation and higher interest rates, brokers said.
   Today the government said new factory orders for durable goods
jumped 8.8 percent in June. However, brokers said the figure wasn't
regarded as conclusive, because most of the increase came in
military goods, a category that is often subject to wide
month-by-month fluctuations.
